(nDCacheTLBWays, power_pad).explanation: Increasing the number of TLB ways requires additional hardware structures and transistors, which directly increases the power consumption of pad circuits needed for signal routing and I/O operations;

(nDCacheTLBWays, power_switching).explanation: More TLB ways increase the number of transistors and switching circuits in the cache subsystem, directly leading to higher dynamic power consumption during cache operations;

(nDCacheTLBWays, time).explanation: Increasing TLB associativity can reduce TLB miss rates and improve cache performance, potentially reducing overall execution time for memory-intensive workloads;
